					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You could line them up at the middle instead, since there are less than 22 pins in each half, right?<br /><br /><img src="http://i51.tinypic.com/15gwidy.png" alt="Image" /></div>
<br />
<br />No, that will not work.  If you lined up the middle perfectly, meaning pin 18, then 11 away from it in either direction you will have a shift of 11 * 0.04 = 0.44mm.  That is a total shift from pin 7 to 29 of 0.88, which is too much.   Remember, the error is in the same direction on both sides.  Ben Heck got around this by splitting the connector in half, thereby sending half the error to the left and half to the right, which does work.  That is also the way your picture above is drawn (error to left of arrows accumulating to left, error on the right accumulating to the right).</div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=29">teaguecl</a> on Fri Jun 24, 2011 1:35 pm, edited 2 times in total.</span>
